HANGMAN(6)

NNAAMMEE
     hhaannggmmaann â€” computer version of the
     game hangman

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
     hhaannggmmaann [--dd _w_o_r_d_l_i_s_t]
     [--mm _m_i_n_l_e_n]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     In hhaannggmmaann, the computer picks a word from
     the on-line word list and you must try to guess it.
     The computer keeps track of which letters have been
     guessed and how many wrong guesses you have made on the
     screen in a graphic fashion.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
     --dd    Use the specified _w_o_r_d_l_i_s_t
     instead of the default one named below.

     --mm    Set the minimum word length to use.  The default
     is 6 letters.

FFIILLEESS
     /usr/share/dict/words  On-line word list

AAUUTTHHOORRSS
     Ken Arnold

